==English==

===Etymology===
A corruption of ''as sure as ''x'' is ''x.

===Adverb===
'''[[sure]] [[as]] [[eggs]] [[is]] [[eggs]]'''

# {{context|simile|colloquial|lang=en}} Absolutely [[certain]].
#: ''At this time of year, '''sure as eggs is eggs''', the TV starts filling with Christmas ads for toys.''

===Usage notes===
* The ''ungrammatical'' '''"is"''' is commonly used in this set phrase.

